  "7.1_quality_rules": [
    "Do not treat Metadata Injector as a policy-consuming component.",
    "Do not treat Queue Runtime Layer as a delegated entity.",
    "Do not collapse delivery-cycle flags into detailed dispatcher feedback reports.",
    "Do not introduce a separate runtime container above Queue Container.",
    "Do not treat Log Level Envelope, Policy Object, Queue Container, Slot, or related state objects as actors unless explicitly promoted in a later taxonomy revision.",
    "Preserve the distinction between primary delegated entity, supporting entity, and governed object.",
    "Preserve system accountability at the Assembler Subsystem level while delegating execution to the narrowest mature architectural carrier.",
    "Preserve typed/template contract doctrine instead of runtime COM interface semantics."
